<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407132>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 26. Oodes japonicus (Bates, 1873) (A–B: male specimen, Japan, Shizuoka Pref., Iwata-shi, Tsurugaike; C–D: male specimen, Laos, Phou Pan Mt.; E–F: female specimen, Japan, Ibaraki Prefecture, Tsukuba City env.; G: female specimen, same locality). A, C: median lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view; B, D: same, dorsal view; E: left gonocoxite, ventral view; F: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, dorsal view; G: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.5 mm (Figs A–D, F–G); = 0.2 mm (Fig. E)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4407132/files/figure.png" .

